Ask HN: Recommend philosophy around consciousness and AI
text:
With 2022 being a huge year for AI via ChatGPT and various diffusion models producing astounding results, I’d like to read thoughtful takes on whether these things are alive in a classical or contrived sense.

Could be philosophers from a world before this technology was a twinkle in the world’s eye up to modern day blogs from folks immersed in this culture. Anything from academic, to fiction, to amateur would be much appreciated.

Tell me what you guys feel about my data platform business
text:
Hey guys, my name is Larry and I'm the founder of Connectome (https://www.connectomesystem.com/).

Connectome is a data platform company based in Hong Kong. We help companies who don't have a strong data capability to consolidate all their data and help them make use of them.

We know there are tools out there but very few of them focus on making it easy for the non-technical to get started with making use of the data. We focus on ingesting and managing the data while many focus on utilizing the data for AI, visualization, etc.

What are you guys initial reaction to this?
